
[1]uranite

   U'RANITE, n. An ore or phosphate of uranium, called also uran-glimmer,
   and uran-mica. It is of a lemon yellow gold color, or yellowish brown,
   sometimes of an apple green or emerald color. It occurs crystallized in
   rectangular prisms, in imperfect octahedrons, &c. Its structure is
   lamellar, and it yields to the knife.

   Uranite is found in primitive earths, in three states, crystallized,
   compact, and pulverulent.
